// ============================================================================
// L4 Track B — sample KQL queries
//
// These are the canonical queries the lab walks attendees through. Azure MCP
// runs KQL against the Log Analytics workspace you deployed in Step 3.
//
// Replace <rg-name> with your actual RG name when running by hand. The agent
// will substitute it automatically when you mention the RG in your prompt.
// ============================================================================


// --- Step 5: AzureActivity for the RG (last hour) ---------------------------
// Note: AzureActivity is only populated if a subscription-level diagnostic
// setting forwards it into your workspace. Fresh sandbox subs usually have
// this; if your query returns no rows, fall back to the Resource Graph query
// at the bottom of this file.
AzureActivity
| where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
| where ResourceGroup =~ "<rg-name>"
| project TimeGenerated, OperationNameValue, ActivityStatusValue, Caller, ResourceProviderValue
| order by TimeGenerated desc
| take 50


// --- Stretch Step 7: storage account blob operations ------------------------
// Requires the stretch step that adds an azurerm_storage_account with a
// diagnostic setting forwarding StorageBlobLogs into this workspace.
StorageBlobLogs
| where TimeGenerated > ago(15m)
| summarize Calls = count() by OperationName, StatusCode
| order by Calls desc


// --- Heartbeat (always present in any LAW) ----------------------------------
// Use this if the agent says "the workspace is empty" — Heartbeat populates
// within ~2 minutes of the workspace existing, so it's the safest "is this
// workspace alive?" probe.
Heartbeat
| where TimeGenerated > ago(10m)
| summarize LastSeen = max(TimeGenerated) by Computer, ResourceGroup


// ============================================================================
// Fallback when AzureActivity is empty: Azure Resource Graph
// Azure MCP exposes the Resource Graph as a separate tool; run this directly
// instead of as KQL-against-LAW.
//
// resources
// | where resourceGroup =~ "<rg-name>"
// | project name, type, location, properties.provisioningState
// ============================================================================
